# Screens Guide

Screen files should follow these guidelines:

1. Use `StatefulWidget` for screens that manage state
2. Keep build methods clean by extracting sections into private methods
3. Implement proper scrolling for content that may overflow
4. Use consistent padding and layout across screens
5. Implement proper state management with `setState`
6. Follow a consistent navigation pattern
7. Handle loading and error states appropriately
8. Use the bottom navigation bar for main app sections

Example screen structure:
```dart
class MissionHubScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  const MissionHubScreen({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  State<MissionHubScreen> createState() => _MissionHubScreenState();
}

class _MissionHubScreenState extends State<MissionHubScreen> {
  // State variables
  
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    // Initialize state
  }
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      backgroundColor: const Color(0xFF121212), // Primary background
      body: SafeArea(
        child: SingleChildScrollView(
          child: Padding(
            padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16.0),
            child: Column(
              crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
              children: [
                _buildHeader(),
                _buildMissionInput(),
                _buildDashboard(),
              ],
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
  
  Widget _buildHeader() {
    // Header implementation
  }
  
  Widget _buildMissionInput() {
    // Mission input implementation
  }
  
  Widget _buildDashboard() {
    // Dashboard implementation
  }
}
